promptVariants.prompt:
Vertical 4:5 canvas, ultra-photorealistic black-and-white 3×3 portrait collage (nine equal square tiles with thin white gutters and a clean outer border, subtle paper texture, light dust and film grain for tactile realism, slight halation on highlights); mood: playful, candid, expressive, photobooth-style energy.
Lighting: single on-axis hard flash just above lens (classic 90s flash pop) with crisp halo shadows; ambient light kept low so flash dominates; small silver bounce card low camera-right to lift cheek and collarbones, black flag camera-left for sculpting shadow; neutral seamless gray or light background for clean contrast.
Camera: 70–85 mm equivalent, head-and-shoulders to mid-chest framing identical across tiles; f/7.1–f/9 for crisp detail, ISO 100–200, 1/200 s at sync speed; focus on near eye; white balance 5200 K before monochrome conversion.
Wardrobe: tight white cotton crop-top T-shirt with round neckline high at the collarbone, short length revealing midriff slightly; smooth, matte texture; no logos; nails clean and glossy; minimal jewelry (thin chain or small hoops).
Hair: loose and natural with a few flyaways catching the flash for texture; makeup luminous and fresh, subtle sheen on lips.
Poses/direction per tile (fun, emotional variety):
, tongue slightly out;
blowing a kiss toward the camera;
mischievous half-smile;
surprised expression, hand over mouth;
showing peace sign or “rock on” gesture;
mock-serious pout with one eyebrow raised;
candid laugh, head slightly back, hair movement;
playful middle-finger gesture with cheeky grin.
Style/mood: 90s/00s photobooth meets editorial flash portrait — bold, tactile, spontaneous, confident.
Post: convert to monochrome with rich mids, smooth highlight roll-off, strong contrast; preserve natural skin texture, crisp fabric detail, and consistent tonality across tiles.add film grain.
